            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/969.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/969.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the tomatoes are roasting, peel and finely chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a very large knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until softened but not coloured</p>",
